 correctly updated. Oddly, when testing a bit more I found that frantically scrolling up and down does seem to update the view and correct number of stars then shows. So indeed something is not properly refreshing.\n\nPS: thanks for offering the feature to couple DND with sleep tracking. I always manually had to enable DND and I am very happy this is no longer needed. Removes friction shortly before going to sleep and trying to wind down.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"e970470018827b6b178556f877e6452433eeadb8d713d3499b58f62b3765b664"},"timestamp":1710070157,"metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHODbKJfs6BzJPczlYWO3c"},"nonce":"3E2vXYDEG8jy9w5KdcQUcRBYYuw=","target":"1e28169f9eaad64b8c0a9a2e3f4f514eb0ef9880689302477fc601adde33d5e5","message":"For a night where a star rating has been set, that star rating is not reflected in the `Past Sleeps` overview page.\n\nThis isn't always reproducible and there are a few variants of the inconsistent behavior:\n\n- for an entry with star rating the overview page shows no star rating at all\n- after changing the star rating a few times an old star rating is shows on the overview page (instead of the latest star rating set and showin when the single nights entry is shown)\n\nThat makes me wonder, if the overview view is not correctly updated. Oddly, when testing a bit more I found that frantically scrolling up and down does seem to update the view and correct number of stars then shows. So indeed something is not properly refreshing and the scrolling seems to force a refresh?\n\nPS: thanks for offering the feature to couple DND with sleep tracking. I always manually had to enable DND and I am very happy this is no longer needed. Removes friction shortly before going to sleep and trying to wind down.","files":null}]}